      {
        "id": 275181,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2007-01-09T12:39:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>- Kobold: I see you need to update some of your information:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"&quot;&quot;Kobold&quot;&quot;\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n \"\"Kobold\"\":</div>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Editing LBA 2 scenes</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You can edit basically everything in the LBA 2 scenes with my LBA Scene Manager, even the move scripts. Only the life scripts yet have to be done properly (it seems like they have a lot more commands than the LBA 1 life scripts).</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"&quot;&quot;Kobold&quot;&quot;\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n \"\"Kobold\"\":</div>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Editing LBA 2 movies</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Actually, you can edit the LBA 2 movies. Just use the <a href=\"http://www.radgametools.com/down/Smacker/SmkTools.exe\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Old Smacker Tools</a>, available for free from the <a href=\"http://www.radgametools.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">RAD Game Tools website</a>.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"&quot;&quot;Kobold&quot;&quot;\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n \"\"Kobold\"\":</div>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Editing</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>We can also edit a lot of other things of LBA 2 as well. We can edit the grids, the grid fragments, the BLLs, the bricks, the sprites, the images, the palettes, the credits (to edit them, use my LBA 2 Credits Manager), the music, the voices, the texts, the font, the raw sprites, and more.</p>\n<p>And Im already working on the LBA 2 3-D model format, so that I can add the support for the LBA 2 3-D models to my LBA Model Manager (and in turn, in future, to my LBA Character Manager). <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
