        "created_at": "2007-01-09T14:05:29.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"OBrasilo\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"10584\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n OBrasilo:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We can also edit a lot of other things of LBA 2 as well. We can edit the grids, the grid fragments, the BLLs, the bricks, the sprites, the images, the palettes, the credits (to edit them, use my LBA 2 Credits Manager), the music, the voices, the texts, the font, the raw sprites, and more.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I knew that.</p>\n<p>I was talking about editing LBA 2 scenes like it is now possible with LBArchitect - seeing what youre doing. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
