      {
        "id": 275309,
        "name": null,
        "username": "xesf",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/xesf/{size}/122_2.png",
        "created_at": "2007-01-10T22:25:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Neko, its not an easy task trying to discover file formats, its like running in the dark. In most of times we try to look first for patterns inside a file the file, and also most of the times they lead us to a answer. This is the kind of things which we need to practice a lot and also know other game file formats for example which in most of the times use the same pattern concept :).</p>\n<p>About LBA2 :), well, the way I did the LBAnimator Studio I can also make a similar program to load and edit LBA2 outside scenes but that takes some good time. Another thing which may be really difficult to get is the LBA2 script. You can see that only after 2 years I start the program, I finally manage to read and save the scripts well, and for LBA2, the scripts are much complicated, because the engine let us use lots of new things LBA1 doesnt allow. Making tools to full modify LBA2 is an hard task and take lots of time, and I can say we wont see it in a near future. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/face_with_diagonal_mouth.png?v=12\" title=\":face_with_diagonal_mouth:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":face_with_diagonal_mouth:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>About making LBA1 harder. I start some months ago a thread in this forum about that and also did a little example :), which was to give to the Swimming Pool some extra SuperGros, which gives another difficult level to the game.<br>\nWe can now easily do that thing, we just need to get a time to do it, and patience to make it in all game scenes</p>",
        "post_number": 10,
        "post_type": 1,
